Author: scifichick774<br>
Rating: R<br>
Category: Chloe/Lex R/D<br>
Spoilers: Through the season one finale. Sequel to Unacceptable.<br>
Summary: Chloe and Lex adjust to married life.<br>
Disclaimer: Not mine, no infringement intended, please don’t sue.<br>
Feedback: Yes please.<br>
Archival: Go ahead, just let me know where.<br>
Author’s Note: Sorry it’s taken me so long to get this out to you guys. I had horrible writer’s block when trying to decide how (and if) to continue this story. That said, if this sucks, I’m sorry. I’m doing my best working with a muse who hates me.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
“Are you sure we have to go to this?” Lex asked as he finished knotting his tie. He already knew what she was going to say, but it didn’t hurt to try and get out of it. The Kents had invited them to their Christmas party. He practically groaned when they received the invitation in the mail. Chloe and Clark were getting along again, but he suspected that Clark’s feelings toward Chloe had only grown with time, and Clark became increasingly protective of her as her pregnancy progressed. Chloe stepped out of the bathroom and Lex scanned over her body with appreciation. She rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“I’m sure,” she answered his previous question and didn’t give any other acknowledgement to his leer. It seemed to happen even more since they had gotten married, almost like he was sending a subconscious signal to any other males that she was his. She was wearing a dark red dress and small dangly garnet earrings. He pulled her into his embrace and leaned down to kiss her. She smiled as they pulled apart. “We don’t have to stay long,” she said to console him. He grinned.<br>
<br>
“Thank God,” he muttered. The drive to the Kent farm went smoothly, despite the snow on the roads. Clark was standing by the window waiting to see them pull up and Lana walked over to him and flashed a bright smile.<br>
<br>
“I’m sure she’s fine,” she said as she touched his arm.<br>
<br>
“The roads are bad,” Clark responded with a frown. She nodded.<br>
<br>
“Lex has gotten to be a much safer driver since Chloe got pregnant,” she reminded him. He sulked his shoulders forward a little in a defeated movement.<br>
<br>
“I guess.” He saw the headlights from their SUV come down the drive and he smiled. Lana rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Told you so,” she teased. Clark and Lana went outside to greet them. Clark rushed to open the door for Chloe and offered her his hand to help her get out. Lex frowned, but didn’t say anything. Chloe gave Clark and Lana warm hugs. “You look great Chloe.” Chloe smiled. Lana had actually grown on her, especially since she seemed to take the edge off of Lex’s jealousy about Clark whenever she was around.<br>
<br>
“Thanks, you too. Now let’s get inside, because I’m freezing,” she laughed and Lex placed his hand on the small of her back as they walked inside. Jonathan frowned at Lex, but Martha grinned at him and came over to give Chloe a hug.<br>
<br>
“How are you feeling?” She asked in a worried voice and placed her hand on Chloe’s protruding stomach.<br>
<br>
“I’m fine. Baby’s good too, all of the tests have shown that nothing’s wrong,” she responded. A flood of relief washed over Martha’s features.<br>
<br>
“Oh, I’m so glad.” She turned to Clark. “Could you fix her a plate?” He nodded and went over toward the buffet.<br>
<br>
“I’m not really that hungry,” Chloe argued. Martha shook her head; she wasn’t going to hear any of it.<br>
<br>
“You need to keep your energy up, and you’re eating for two now remember,” she said in a motherly tone. Chloe rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“That’s what Lex keeps telling me too,” she grinned at her husband who returned the gesture. He shrugged.<br>
<br>
“She never listens to me either,” Lex said dryly. Chloe playfully hit his arm and he chuckled. Martha frowned at Lex.<br>
<br>
“She’s stubborn. You should have someone looking after her,” she said. Chloe looked at her in disbelief.<br>
<br>
“I’m perfectly capable of taking care of myself, but thank you for your concern Mrs. Kent,” she stated. Lex had to bite back a laugh. He knew Martha had been suggesting that Clark or she come over to check on Chloe more often than they already were. He didn’t like how Clark, Lana, or Martha seemed to ‘be in the neighborhood’ almost all of the time as it was. He was thankful that she had graduated early. At least he didn’t have to worry about Clark clamoring all over her at school. Martha Kent sighed.<br>
<br>
“If you change your mind, be sure to call me,” she finally gave in. Chloe nodded and smiled. Clark came over with a full plate of food and Chloe’s eyes grew wide.<br>
<br>
“That’s for you right?” She asked. He smiled brightly and held it out for her. Chloe groaned and Lex chuckled. “What is it with people and feeding this kid? He’s like four pounds.” Lex arched an eyebrow at her.<br>
<br>
“He?” Chloe shrugged.<br>
<br>
“I don’t feel comfortable saying ‘it’,” she explained.<br>
<br>
“Uh huh,” he said unconvinced. She sighed and looked at him.<br>
<br>
“I promised I wouldn’t find out unless you were there with me,” she reminded him in an exasperated voice. He smirked and nodded. Chloe finally took the plate from Clark. Martha wandered off to talk to other guests and Chloe smiled at Clark. “You should go talk to other people too Clark, it is your party.” Clark looked hesitant.<br>
<br>
“We are capable of entertaining ourselves you know,” Lex added in a neutral tone. Clark briefly glanced down at Chloe’s stomach and then back up at Lex.<br>
<br>
“I’m aware of that,” he answered in a cynical tone. Lex grinned and Chloe started laughing. Chloe handed the plate of food back to Clark and he looked confused.<br>
<br>
“I’m sorry Clark. I thought I had enough energy to do this tonight, but…” Clark nodded and smiled in understanding.<br>
<br>
“It’s okay. Do you want to lie down upstairs?” He motioned to the stairs with his head. “You could take my bed,” he offered. Lex glared at him.<br>
<br>
“I think we should just go home,” he said while keeping the threatening eye contact. Clark grinned sheepishly at Chloe.<br>
<br>
“Okay. See you tomorrow?” He asked. Chloe nodded and he walked them to the door. Clark leaned down and gave her a small kiss on her mouth, catching her completely by surprise. Lex growled and Clark smiled and pointed to the mistletoe hanging at the top of the door. Chloe rolled her eyes and grabbed Lex’s hand, dragging him out of the party and toward their car.<br>
<br>
“You know he planned that don’t you?” Lex asked and opened her door for her.<br>
<br>
“Obviously,” she said sarcastically, “Because every guy wants to hit on a girl who’s pregnant with someone else’s child, and oh yeah, who’s married to the father of the child.” He felt the grin tugging at the corners of his lips. She was right. He had no reason to worry about Clark Kent, he was no threat. So why did he still have a nagging feeling in his gut that he was?<br>
