<br>
“What happened? Has there been a change?” Lex demanded. She sighed.<br>
<br>
“Maybe you should sit down,” she recommended. His warning glare told her not to push it. “Alright. Yes, there has been a change. Remarkably, she woke up.” The expression on Lex’s face changed from panic to hope.<br>
<br>
“I want to see her,” he stated. She frowned.<br>
<br>
“It’s not that simple,” she said and then paused. “She doesn’t remember the accident.”<br>
<br>
“Good,” he said. She shook her head.<br>
<br>
“Not good. She doesn’t remember a lot of things,” Dr. Schafer said. Clark furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“Like what?” He asked. Dr. Schafer ran a hand through her hair and took a deep breath.<br>
<br>
“She doesn’t remember being married or being pregnant, she doesn’t remember the last time she was in the ER.” She paused again and looked at Lex. “I told her that you would go to her room, that it might help trigger memories.” He nodded.<br>
<br>
“Of course,” he said. Clark frowned.<br>
<br>
“I want to go too,” he said. Lex glared at him, but the doctor nodded.<br>
<br>
“Actually, that’s a good idea. You’ve been friends for a long time right?” He nodded. “She needs anything that can help jog memories, friends, pictures, stories of things that have happened.” Lex growled, making Dr. Schafer swing her head back toward him.<br>
<br>
“She doesn’t need to see him for those things,” he argued. She plastered on her bravest face.<br>
<br>
“She does. She needs you and all of her friends and family to help if she’s going to get better,” she stated in a firm voice. “But, it would be a good idea if you saw her separately.”<br>
<br>
“Which room?” Lex asked.<br>
<br>
“She’s in critical care, you’ll have to have a nurse take you,” Dr. Schafer said. Lex gave her an impatient expression and she motioned for him to follow her. Clark watched Lex leave with the doctor and Jonathan came over to him and put a hand on his shoulder.<br>
<br>
“What are you thinking son?” He asked. Clark turned to him with a strange look on his face. “Clark?” His tone was warning and Clark grinned.<br>
<br>
“I can get her back Dad,” he said. Jonathan looked down while he shook his head.<br>
<br>
“She’s married to Lex,” he reminded him.<br>
<br>
“But she doesn’t remember being married to Lex.”<br>
<br>
“It doesn’t matter whether she remembers it or not Clark, he’s her husband.”<br>
<br>
“No,” Clark said as he shook his head emphatically. “I have a plan.” Jonathan frowned.<br>
<br>
“Get that gleam out of your eye,” he warned. Clark smiled.<br>
<br>
“This is my last chance Dad, I have to take it.”<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Lex knocked on Chloe’s door and let himself in. She looked up at him. He looked concerned for her, an expression she never thought she’d see on Lex Luthor, especially not for her. He sat down next to her and brought her hand up to his lips. She opened her mouth slightly at the intimacy of the action, but quickly closed it when she remembered being called Mrs. Luthor. She still eyed him warily though. He stroked some stray hair behind her ear.<br>
<br>
“They said you’re having trouble remembering some things,” he said matter-of-factly. She nodded once. “What’s the last thing you remember before waking up here?” She closed her eyes as she thought. He tried not to give into his urge to kiss her. The doctor said that she might feel more alienated from him if he attempted any intimate gestures. She didn’t remember being married to him, so in all likelihood, she would be frightened rather than relaxed by the actions. He grimaced a little when he realized he had already kissed her hand. He shook it off as she opened her eyes.<br>
<br>
“I was getting ready for the dance,” she said. Lex inwardly cringed.<br>
<br>
“What dance?”<br>
<br>
“The spring formal,” she said. “I remember putting on my dress, but nothing after that.” She gave a sardonic half laugh. “Guess I won’t be fitting back in that dress any time soon huh?” His lips curled upward.<br>
<br>
“I’m sure you’ll be back down to your regular size in no time,” he said reassuringly. “Besides, you burned that dress.” Her eyes grew wide. “Bad memories,” he explained. She furrowed her brow.<br>
<br>
“What happened?” She asked. He sighed. He didn’t really want to go into a story about how his wife was mooning over Clark Kent, and that now he returned her old feelings.<br>
<br>
“You and Clark went to the dance, there was tornado alert, he left the dance to save Lana from a twister,” he rambled off the short version. She looked horrified, but not for the reason Lex thought.<br>
<br>
“Is she okay?” She asked.<br>
<br>
“Who?”<br>
<br>
“Lana,” she said. He rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
“She’s fine,” he said. Chloe nodded and sadness radiated from her.<br>
<br>
“So, I guess that… they’re probably together now then,” she said hesitantly. Lex frowned.<br>
<br>
“No.”<br>
<br>
“No?!” Chloe repeated loudly. “God! He saves her life and she can’t get over Whitney?” She shook her head in disbelief. He cocked an eyebrow at her.<br>
<br>
“Actually, she’s seeing Pete,” Lex said. Chloe’s eyes grew wide again and she was silent, not being able to come up with the words to express her feelings at the news. ‘Okay Chloe, time to change the topic,’ she thought to herself.<br>
<br>
“So, um, how did you and I…?” She motioned between them with her hand. He smiled. ‘Lex Luthor can smile?’<br>
<br>
“You were pretty upset about Clark leaving you at the dance to find Lana,” he started.<br>
<br>
“Wait a second. He just left me there?” She asked. He nodded. She pushed her lips together. “Jerk,” she mumbled. He laughed.<br>
<br>
“That was your impression then too,” he said. She smiled.<br>
<br>
“Okay. So us?”<br>
<br>
“I took advantage of the situation,” he said without remorse. She looked at him with a half shocked expression, but he just shrugged. “I liked you, I saw an opportunity, and I took it.”<br>
<br>
“Nice,” she said sarcastically. He grinned.<br>
<br>
“It was a little more romantic than that,” he conceded. She looked at her belly and then back at him.<br>
<br>
“I certainly hope so,” she said. He smiled and absently stroked her stomach in a loving manner.<br>
<br>
“How are you feeling? Do you need anything?” He asked. She shook her head.<br>
<br>
“They can’t give me anything more than Tylenol for the pain because of the baby,” she said. “So unless you can invent something that can get rid of the pain but still be okay for pregnant women, then no.” He smirked.<br>
<br>
“I’ll see what I can do,” he said. Lex paused, not wanting to ask the question that he knew he needed to ask her. “Do you want to see Clark?”<br>
<br>
