<br>
“I know you’re not my biggest fan Mr. Kent, but…”<br>
<br>
“Lex,” Jonathan interrupted. He paused while thinking of the right words to say. “It’s true, I don’t particularly care for you, but since Chloe is your wife, I think you have a right to know.”<br>
<br>
“A right to know what?” Lex asked. Jonathan sighed and sat down next to him.<br>
<br>
“Clark thinks this is his last chance to get Chloe back,” he said. Lex growled and Jonathan held up a hand. “Save it. I agree with you.” Lex looked at him questioningly. “He said he has a plan to get her back, he didn’t share the details, but I thought you should know. Believe it or not, I actually think being with Chloe has made you a better man.” Lex nodded in agreement.<br>
<br>
“He didn’t say anything about his ‘plan’?” Lex asked. Jonathan shook his head.<br>
<br>
“No. I have a bad feeling it has to do with lying to Chloe while she can’t remember though.” Lex felt ill. He might be able to pull it off, at least until Chloe got her memory back, and by then… damn him! Lex got up and started to run down the hall toward Chloe’s room. He was stopped by a large security guard who reminded him that only one visitor was allowed at a time in that area, but that he would be informed of when the other man left. Lex desperately tried to bribe the man, but was promptly sent back to the waiting room. Jonathan gave him a sympathetic look.<br>
<br>
“Wouldn’t let you in huh?” He asked. Lex grumbled.<br>
<br>
“Maybe if I buy their damn hospital I could change all of the policies they have around here,” he said, although more to himself than to Jonathan. The older man gave him a compensatory grin.<br>
<br>
“Don’t worry. Even with amnesia, Chloe’s a bright young woman. She’s always been able to tell when Clark was lying. Everything will be alright,” he said reassuringly. Lex closed his eyes and breathed. He hoped Jonathan was right.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Clark walked into Chloe’s room and smiled at her.<br>
<br>
“How are you?” He asked, dropping his head slightly and then raising his eyes to give his best puppy dog look. She smiled.<br>
<br>
“Tired and in pain, but there’s not a lot they can do about it,” she said. He sat down in the chair next to her bed.<br>
<br>
“They said that you have amnesia,” he said. Chloe frowned.<br>
<br>
“They also said it’s also probably temporary and that people or images might bring back my memory,” she said. “It’s weird, when Lex was telling me some things, I didn’t remember them, but…”<br>
<br>
“But?” Clark tried to hide the worry from his voice.<br>
<br>
“But I felt safe when he was here, loved even. Weird?” She asked. He frowned and shook his head.<br>
<br>
“No. He loves you,” he said. She grinned.<br>
<br>
“So I guess you never thought I’d end up marrying your best friend did you?” She asked. He raised his eyebrows.<br>
<br>
“Lex and I aren’t really best friends any more,” he admitted. Chloe’s face fell.<br>
<br>
“Oh?”<br>
<br>
“And actually, I hoped you would end up marrying me,” he said. She arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“Yeah right,” she said sarcastically. He looked into her eyes and she shrank back a little at his overwhelming expression. “Oh.” He took her hand in his.<br>
<br>
“It’s okay though Chlo, I understand,” he said, looking at their hands together instead of in her eyes. “You had to do what was best for the baby,” he paused, still avoiding eye contact. “Our baby,” he said quietly. Chloe’s eyes grew wide in horror.<br>
<br>
“What?!” She yelled. He stroked her hand.<br>
<br>
“Shhh. It’s okay. Everything’s going to be okay,” he said. He seemed so sincere. Why would she marry Lex if she was pregnant with Clark’s baby? It made no sense. Then she realized that he still wasn’t looking her in the eyes. She narrowed her eyes at him as a familiar suspicious feeling swept over her.<br>
<br>
“You’re lying,” she said. She didn’t say it in an accusatory manner; she was simply stating a fact. “Why are you lying?” He finally looked up at her and she saw his wet eyes. “Clark?”<br>
<br>
“God Chloe, I love you,” he said. He brought her hand to his mouth and kissed it, and much to her surprise, she quickly jerked it away. It felt wrong. He felt wrong. “I just wanted us to be together. I thought, if you couldn’t remember, that…”<br>
<br>
“That you would just rewrite history?” She asked and shook her head. “You don’t have the power to turn back time Clark. And even if you did, I get the feeling that I wouldn’t want you to.” He looked stunned and she grinned softly. “I’m not mad at you. I should be, but I’m not. And even though I don’t remember being married to Lex,” she paused. “This is going to sound so corny. I think my soul remembers him Clark. I’ve never felt the way I did when he was in the room with me.” Clark frowned and nodded, and then smiled meekly.<br>
<br>
“At least you don’t remember me trying to stop your wedding,” he joked. Her mouth dropped open.<br>
<br>
“You didn’t?!”<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” he smiled, “I did. But it didn’t work, you got married anyway. And you ended up forgiving me.” She looked at him in disbelief.<br>
<br>
“Did I have a nice dress?” She asked. He laughed.<br>
<br>
“Gorgeous,” he said. She laid her head against her pillow with a smug look on her face.<br>
<br>
“Good.”<br>
<br>
“So I guess there’s no chance of…”<br>
<br>
“You and me?” She finished. Clark nodded. “I don’t think so,” she admitted. “Do you believe in destiny?” He gave her a confused look at the change of topic.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know, I’ve never really thought about it.”<br>
<br>
“I didn’t use to. But then I met you,” she said. Clark smiled. “I think I always knew that you were destined for great things, I think that’s part of the reason I liked you. But now…”<br>
<br>
“But now you think I’m just some jerk who tried to stop your wedding?” He asked, half-kidding. She laughed.<br>
<br>
“No. I still think you’re destined for great things Clark, but I also know that we’re only supposed to be friends in that destiny. When Lex was in here, I may not have remembered, but I felt like I belonged with him.” Clark gave her a sad grin.<br>
<br>
“I understand.”<br>
<br>
“I know,” she said as she gave his hand a squeeze. “And thanks.”<br>
