<br>
“What did you do?” He asked accusingly. “Your dad told me about your ‘plan’. What did you do?” Clark looked down.<br>
<br>
“It doesn’t matter,” he said.<br>
<br>
“What did you do?” Lex repeated with more anger in his voice. Clark sighed.<br>
<br>
“I told her…” he shook his head. “It doesn’t matter Lex. She didn’t believe me.” Lex stood there waiting for an explanation. “I told her that it wasn’t your baby,” he said under his breath. Lex clenched his hands into fists but Clark walked past him and went to sit down. Lex turned around to continue the beginning of what he thought would be a fight. Clark ran his hands over his face and through his hair. “I can’t believe it,” he said to himself. “She doesn’t remember anything, but she still thinks she belongs with you.” His tone indicated his disbelief at the situation. Lex’s hands fell from their clenched form and he eyed Clark warily.<br>
<br>
“Did she say that?” He couldn’t hide the hope in his voice. Clark looked up at him and gave a small smile.<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” he confirmed. He leaned back in his chair. “And in case you’re wondering, she totally called me on the lie.” Lex grinned in delight. Clark rolled his eyes. “She said she wants to see you again if it’s not too late.” Lex nodded once and turned to go down the hallway. “Lex?” He turned back around.<br>
<br>
“Clark.”<br>
<br>
“You’re a lucky guy,” he said sadly. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
“Luck has nothing to do with it,” he responded. Lex turned around and walked down the hall to see his wife. Clark closed his eyes and the last thing his father heard him mumble was something about destiny.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Lex knocked gently on Chloe’s door, but there was no answer. He walked in slowly and silently and sat down on the chair beside her bed. Her eyes were closed, and despite the bruises, bandages, the IV, and the various machines she was hooked up to, she looked so peaceful. He took her hand in his and stroked it gently. Her eyes fluttered open and she moved her head to look at him.<br>
<br>
“I’m sorry,” he said in a hushed voice. “I didn’t mean to wake you.” She grinned.<br>
<br>
“No problem,” she said. Lex looked at her with nothing but love and concern in his eyes.<br>
<br>
“Clark told me what happened,” he started. She chuckled.<br>
<br>
“Yeah. I’ve known him for what seems like forever. What made him think he could lie to me like that?” She asked.<br>
<br>
“He loves you,” he said morosely.<br>
<br>
“He’ll get over it,” she said bluntly. Lex grinned. “And if he doesn’t… well, too bad. I’m taken.” His grin broadened to a smile.<br>
<br>
“You remember?”<br>
<br>
“Bits and pieces are starting to come back, but not all of it,” she said.<br>
<br>
“Give it time,” he said and touched her cheek with the back of his hand. She leaned in to his touch and he grinned. He remembered what the doctors had told him about not initiating any intimate actions with her, but he couldn’t help it. He leaned down and tentatively gave her a soft kiss. She seemed surprised, but responded after just a moment of his lips being pressed against hers. It was sweet at first, but deepened quickly. She ran her hands up his chest and around his neck. He pulled away for a brief second to breathe. She looked at him, a bemused smile on her face.<br>
<br>
“So I guess that’s how we got where we are now huh?” She asked. He smiled.<br>
<br>
“I’d show you more, but I doubt they’d let me get away with it since you just had surgery,” he responded. She laughed.<br>
<br>
“Can I ask you a question?”<br>
<br>
“Anything,” he said sincerely.<br>
<br>
“How did you get me to change my last name?” She asked. He smirked.<br>
<br>
“I can be very persuasive,” he said. She tried to fight down the blush that rose to her cheeks with his innuendo.<br>
<br>
“How much longer do I need to stay here?” She asked, changing the topic. His face became very serious.<br>
<br>
“For a while. You had to have surgery and they’re monitoring the baby because of some damage to the amniotic sac,” he told her. He saw the worried expression on her face and tried to lighten the mood. “Although technically, that was two questions.” She rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Does that mean I can ignore the second answer?”<br>
<br>
“No.”<br>
<br>
“Damn,” she said. He chuckled.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
2 months later<br>
<br>
Chloe gripped into Lex’s hand forcefully as the pain swept through her. Lex cringed.<br>
<br>
“Are you sure we can’t give her drugs?” He asked in a pleading voice. The doctor looked at him and grinned.<br>
<br>
“She’s too far along for that now Mr. Luthor,” the doctor said. “Alright Chloe, when the next contraction comes, I want you to push through a count of ten. Okay?” Chloe nodded dumbly in exhaustion, but the next contraction hit swiftly and the doctor counted to ten slowly as Chloe pushed. “That’s good sweetie, I can see the top of the head now. One more time should do it.” Chloe pushed again when the next contraction came and the doctor unraveled the cord from around the baby’s neck. She used a nasal aspirator and cleared out the mucus from the baby’s nose and mouth and then held the baby up for Chloe and Lex to see. “Congratulations, it’s a boy.” Chloe and Lex both smiled.<br>
<br>
“Can I hold him?” Chloe asked. The doctor nodded.<br>
<br>
“Let us get him cleaned up and take measurements really quick,” she said. Chloe nodded. Lex kissed her forehead.<br>
<br>
“You’re amazing,” he said in awe of what she had just done. She chuckled.<br>
<br>
“Obviously,” she said sarcastically. He leaned down and moved his lips against hers. The nurse cleared her throat and they looked up at her holding their son wrapped in a blanket. Chloe held out her arms and took him into them, snuggling the baby against her chest. Lex held out a finger for the tiny fingers to grab. He smiled.<br>
<br>
“We’re going to have to come up with a name you know,” he said to Chloe.<br>
<br>
“I know,” she agreed. “No L names.” He chuckled.<br>
<br>
“And not Clark,” he added. She smiled as she looked down at the baby.<br>
<br>
“Don’t worry,” she said as she snuggled her nose up against the baby’s cheek. “We’ll think of something.” Lex grinned and leaned down beside her.<br>
<br>
“We would have already thought of something if your mommy wasn’t so picky,” he said. She gave him a mock glare.<br>
<br>
“You’re going to get into this now?” She warned. He smiled.<br>
<br>
“How much longer are you going to argue with me about this?” He teased. The nurse whispered to the doctor.<br>
<br>
“Until I get my way,” Chloe said matter-of-factly.<br>
<br>
“Are they always like this?” She asked. The doctor rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Yes,” she answered. Lex chuckled again.<br>
<br>
“Fine, you can have your way,” he said and kissed her on the cheek. Her smile beamed and her eyes glittered.<br>
<br>
“Really?”<br>
<br>
“Really.” They both looked down at their small son with love and pride. Lex ran a finger delicately along the baby’s cheek. “Welcome to the world Cameron.”<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
